						<div class="postbody">I am designin graphics with the NES limitations for a PC game.
<br />
<br />I am wondering that is it possible on a real NES to use sprites with 4 colors instead of 3 colors + alpha? I know that the first color of all the 4 sprite palettes must be the same color (alpha), but could this be set to some non-transparent color (for example black)?</div>

					
